You know, for being a&nbsp;hermit for&nbsp;the summer-- Metrocon excluded, --I suddenly have a very busy social schedule. 

Kitty's birthday party and Allison's dear-god-we're-going-back-to-school party both happen to be Sunday.&nbsp; 

And suddenly, here I am with conflicting events.&nbsp; 

...My head hurts.&nbsp; 

... 

... 

...I want icecream.

I'm still chilling out at Erin's. We're actually having an inpromptu birthday bash of sorts for her tomorrow.&nbsp;<br /><br />Once again, con recap.<br /><br />

<table cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" width="400" align="center" summary="[ Sam, Emily, the unnamed Envy, the other Al, Michael and myself. ]" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p align="center"><img height="225" alt="[ Sam, Emily, the unnamed Envy, the other Al, Michael and myself. ]" width="300" align="middle" src="http://photos-948.ll.facebook.com/photos-ll-sf2p/v207/118/16/759948948/n759948948_1124725_7380.jpg" /></p></td></tr><tr><td><p align="center">[ Sam, Emily, the Envy, the other Al, Michael and myself. ]</p></td></tr></tbody></table>

<br /><br /><strong>Day 3.<br /><br /></strong>Feeling more than slightly unconcious for most of the morning, I don't really remember much except that I woke up late with Grant poking his head into my room as Mum dropped off an offering of Starbucks and a bagel. I ended up dragging myself out of bed just enough to eat said bagel-- which had been cream-cheesed while I was attempting to down myself in my coffee --and getting paritally changed into movie!Al before realizing that both coffee and breakfast together makes me sick.&nbsp;<br /><br />Tossed out the last, bite-sized piece of bagel and unhappily dragged myself to the other hotel room, where I promptly stole Megan's spot on one of the beds.&nbsp;<br /><br />Apparently I make a pretty femme!movie!Al,&nbsp;considering I hadn't quite buttoned up the shirt yet and I hadn't stolen a hairtie from anyone for the wig, and I was conned into staying that way for another hour until we left for the con.&nbsp;<br /><br />We skipped off to the con with a Gurren Lagann group, a two-man Hellsing group, and myself as movie!Al.&nbsp;<br /><br />I'd lost Grant as my movie!Ed, so I dragged Josh the Second along as my non-cosplay buddy while I looked for another movie!Al that was supposed to be attending on Sunday. It's actually kind of amusing in a way, as we spent most of the time outside of the chess match looking for her, and found her two minutes before I actually had to leave.<br /><br />I ended up meeting up with Emily, the anime!+movie!Winry from the previous day, and we happily skipped off together to watch the chess match. We found ourselves more than slightly annoyed that not <em>only</em> were the Sins killed off, but all of the FMA cast was, once again, dead by the end of the show.<br /><br />Skipped out in a disappointed manner and was dragged off for a few more photos before running back into Sam, the automail!Ed from the day before, and the Envy who still remains unnamed. Enlisted their help in finding the other Al and in making me a sign that stated that I had lost my <strike>short</strike>&nbsp;older brother.<br /><br />Somewhere inbetween goodbye hugs and last minute photos, my sign went MIA, actually. =/<br /><br />Has anyone seen that, by the way?<br /><br />After Erin and I picked up our luggage stowed away&nbsp;with the hotel, we ran off to the car and drove back to Sarasota, where we remain happily ever after.<br /><br />&nbsp;

So-- today was a mess.&nbsp;

Research paper was due today, which obviously ended in disaster. The usual.

It's Graduation, so there are no seniors, and the sophmores are all skipping. Which means we've got freshmen and us, and that's pretty much it. The school is fantastically empty.&nbsp;

Which means that we've watched movies. All day.&nbsp;

Huzzah?
